reviews.review_text: My husband and I found this place when we wanted some late night food. We absolutely loved the live music, it was such an inviting place. The food was fantastic and so authentic! We loved getting to have some Indian street food that we ve never had before. Everything was so good we went back the next day for brunch! A few things were quite spicy and I needed to get some yogurt to go with it, but I wouldn t change a thing. It was SO DELICIOUS!!!! We ll definitely want to come back here whenever we are in Vancouver.

This is such a cute underground cozy spot. Super authentic masala chai, 100% recommend. We also tried some of the street food options like aloo tiki burger, chat papri and gol gappa. We already want to come back for more! Recommend!

Dilli Heights Bistro in Vancouver is a culinary delight! The golgappe sent my taste buds on a journey to Delhi, evoking the authentic flavors of the bustling streets. The chicken and veg momos were a true gastronomic pleasure, leaving me craving for more. And the vada pav? It was nothing short of a fantabulous explosion of flavors. This restaurant is a must-visit for every foodie seeking an exquisite taste of Delhi in the heart of Vancouver. Vegetarian options: So many options to choose from
Reached there late around 11:00 PM, a great place to hang out late night, food tasted good, they had live music playing Bollywood songs.

Amazingly curated menu, great ambience and the taste is just cherry on the top. Loved all the dishes we ordered, the chaat was really really good and momos were really yum. DEFINITELY A MUST VISIT IF IN DOWNTOWN VANCOUVER!!!!!!!!! Vegetarian options: They are the besttttt

Lovely place, loved trying some new foods! The chai was delicious, perfect place for studying while enjoying live music. Thanks Vani and Kartik for an amazing experience. Also, Udit is an amazing singer, this just made the evening even better

I have been to this newly opened cafe before and loved their samosa chaat and butter chicken platter. The ambience is so cozy that you could sit and have chit chat while enjoying the flavourful food. Today we had a take away from them , and let me tell you how amazing was the chicken sandwich. Samosa chat was much needed in this gloomy rainy day. We will  definitely go again along with our friends as the location is super convenient in downtown. Would love to try their drinks too as it seems like an interesting menu. Service is always top notch  and perfect. Photos can t do the justice as it s a takeaway, but quantity was more then good enough for two people. Highly recommended.

Visited this great cozy place and had Rajma Rice Bowl, Veg Momos. I must say, they got the best vibe and food tasted exactly as they say  Indian Style .  tasted just like freshly made and was amazing. I will recommend this place to everyone who really want to try Indian Style and freshly made food

A perfect place to spend time with your near and dear ones. If you are missing and craving for Delhi style street food then this is the right place to step by in and enjoy the scrumptious food items to satisfy your taste buds.

I recently had the pleasure of dining at Delhi Heights, and I must say it was an incredible experience from start to finish. This bistro brings the vibrant flavors of Delhi right here to Vancouver, and it exceeded all my expectations. The staff members are incredibly friendly, knowledgeable, and attentive. They made sure our visit was nothing short of exceptional, providing excellent recommendations and ensuring all our needs were met. Now, lets talk about the food, The menu is thoughtfully curated, featuring a wide variety of vegetarian and non-vegetarian options to suit every palate. The flavors were rich, vibrant, and perfectly balanced, taking my taste buds on an unforgettable journey. Whether youre craving authentic Indian cuisine or looking to explore new flavors, Delhi Heights is an absolute gem in Vancouver. The combination of exceptional food, attentive service, and inviting atmosphere makes it a must-visit bistro. I cant recommend this place enough!

One of the best places to have chat, It is the closest to Indian food I have had in Vancouver. Flavour has not been toned down. We tried fried momo, aaloo tikki burger, gol gappa. Loved everything. Must visit. Go early though gets crowed!

The place brings a plethora of new flavours to downtown Vancouver. The food is served hot and fresh. It is brimming with different flavours and as a long time customer of the place they have improved their menu quite a lot. They staff is really helpful and understands your unique food palette. They provide food in these bowls that double as a storage container if you decide to take the food home. overall, the staff is very helpful and the vibe of the place is immaculate.
had the veggie rice bowl, coffee frappe, pesto croissant, and the chicken korma sandwich. all were delicious and the portions are good! would recommend you guys to try if you are in the area
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thanks Matthew! Really happy to know that you enjoyed the food!

reviews.review_text: Its a really good place for Indian snacks food. And you can get good burgers, wraps and shake. Vani and two other cooks were amazing and friendly. They served very well and on point customer service.

This is a proper cosy Cafe right beside MacLeods books on Richards Street. We ordered the bowls and they tasted fresh and absolutely delicious. Looks like they slashed the prices recently and have very aggressive pricing now(quite atypical of downtown eateries). The value for money is quite good. Well, if its comparatively easier on my pocket, Im not complaining. Highly recommend if you are out and about in the area and looking for an excellent option for Indian food.

Dilli Heights is a just-opened cafe serving fresh Indian fast-casual food and drink, and some Canadian-style muffins and cookies. It s located below street level down a flight of stairs, so you might miss it if you re not looking. I didn t notice any way to get to the restaurant besides the staircase but I wasn t really looking so maybe there s something. I had a very lovely experience from the minute I walked through the door. I was the only customer at the time and the man working, Sayed, greeted me very warmly and was patient while I looked at the baked goods and gave me a good explanation of the different types of chai they offer (you can pretty much pick and choose the spice combination you want - cool). After I ordered, he invited me to sit wherever I like, and when I hesitated on deciding which table would be optimal, he suggested I make myself comfortable on a single-seat couch in the corner. I ordered a paneer butter masala rice bowl, an oat cookie, and a masala chai. The cookie and chai were actually brought out first after the cookie was warmed up. The cookie was very soft and a little buttery with lots of different crunchy seeds. The chai was excellent - no chai latte business, this is actual strained Indian chai. This one was on the mellow side and super smooth. I usually like bolder flavours but the subtlety of this was admittedly nice. Then my rice bowl was brought out! I was pleasantly surprised by both the size of this and the neat presentation. The curry was rich and vibrant but not heavy, and there were lots of paneer chunks! The spice level was perfect - there was just enough to add the right flavour. The tomato and onion salad was very fresh and the rice was also cooked perfectly. Everything was just right on. Although the food was slightly more expensive than what you might pay at the average fast-casual restaurant, the quality and portion totally justified it. After I finished was ready to head out, Sayed asked me how everything was and offered to clean everything up for me. The food in itself would have easily been enough to get this place 5 stars from me, but the level of care and attention to detail from Sayed made this a very memorable experience. Do these wonderful business a favour and treat yourself to a delicious meal here!
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thank you so much Dana! We are humbled with your review and the kind words. Hoping to see you again soon!

reviews.review_text: Place has a cool vibe and food is very delicious. Usually busy on weekends but can easily get table on weekdays. Fav place to eat street food

I had visited over here with my family and tried there spicy chicken burger and both veg and chicken momos. Everything was top notch from there juicy burger to there authentic momos with quick delivery and the staff was excellent at there service and with their friendliness and will surely visit them again and recommend others as well.

Very nice experience, Kritika gave her best customer services to us , as we re there to celebrate our friend s birthday and the food preparation team also gave its best. Overall we re overwhelmed by spending our time there. Will recommend you to go there with your friends too.

Great food - we ordered Rajma Chawal, pani-puri and steamed momos. Everything tasted good, but for me Rajma Chawal felt like home! Amazing Host - Ishmita and Sumit really did an amazing service hosting! They both were engaging, patient and always had a warm smile - even when I could see the cafe was getting busy. Atmosphere - Loved it ! Simple and Familiar.

I love the food. I ordered masala chai and pav bhaji. Taste was authentic just like delhi street food. I never had such a good taste in Vancouver. Staffs are friendly. I love their hospitality. Overall, my experience was good with Delhi heights Bistro.
We visited Vancouver and went to this cute little place for dinner. We tried rajma and chicken bowls with rice. The food was delicious. Must visit. They have momos, chaat, Fanta.

omg what a day!!!! i mean awesome vibes with staff and musician we really really enjoy the atmosphere food, songs and service of staff. they really friendly. The girl who is working in the front she is really superb.. #ReallyDelhivibes #dillivibes

Amazing service and staff! We went around 11:30 at night and we were prepared that we will probably have to leave since it was almost closing time. But the girl working there, Kritika told us they will allow us to stay and made amazing food for us. Kritika, Sam and Kartik were the people working at that time and if you go to Dilli heights theyll not disappoint you     Thanks for serving us last night. :)

I had an exceptional dining experience at Dilli Heights Bistro in downtown Vancouver. From the moment we walked in, we were greeted by the wonderful server, Vani, who made our evening truly memorable. The chef, Sumit, worked his culinary magic to prepare a delightful spread for us. We started with the momos, which were incredibly flavorful, followed by the mouthwatering pav bhaji and aloo chaat that left our taste buds dancing with joy. The star of the show was undoubtedly the amazing elaichi chai, a perfect blend of spices that warmed our hearts. Not only was the food outstanding, but the service was impeccable. Vanis attentive and friendly approach added a personal touch to the evening, making us feel right at home. Dilli Heights Bistro is a true gem in Vancouvers dining scene. I highly recommend it to anyone looking for a taste of authentic and delicious Indian cuisine, served with a smile. Kudos to Vani, Sumit, and the entire team for making our visit unforgettable!

Food was good but had to say the service was just wow. The girl ( Kritika) working at front was very sweet and helping. She also offered us another drink cuz our drink was not good. Really great job done by boys (Sam & kartik).
First time trying this place out and I was happy with the result. Lovely service, good prices and great flavour. Will be back! Food

Heard about this newly opened cafe in downtown Vancouver from a friend. Stopped by today for a quick lunch before work. Honestly speaking, I didn t have this much delicious chana rice bowl in a long time. And the choco-fudge shake was so yummm!!! Their staff was welcoming. Will definitely go back to try the other menu options.

I am Living in Vancouver since birth and I have tried almost all the Indian restaurants but this one hits different everytime I visit. Mostly I visit this place for Butter Chicken and Chicken Masala Roll. Also the chicken momos especially steamed are awesome. I cant describe in words how I love these items. An absolute gem in Vancouver! The Indian cafe and bistro captivated me with its top-notch ambiance that instantly transported me. The flavors of the food were simply divine, each bite a delightful explosion of taste. A definite must-visit for anyone craving an exceptional culinary experience.

Was passing through Richards street and saw this new cafe with a New Delhi touch. Their butter chicken rice bowl is a must try. Staff and the owners are really friendly . Will definitely visit again to try their other dishes.
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thank you Nimit for your kind review!

reviews.review_text: Visited the place yesterday and i must say the food was delicious. A special mention for the server named vani, she was very polite and helpful. I recommend everyone who s reading this to visit this place. Love the vibe.
Kritika s hospitality and Sam s skill were absolutely phenomenal. I have been missing and craving Indian food for a while but rest assured today my senses have been satiated.

I have been going to this place from 2 months and here are few things I wanna talk about. First the food. It is delicious. I am a vegetarian and there are many options available for us and from these I have tried Rice Bowls, Burgers, Momos, Pav bhaji and all the chaats. From all of them Aloo tikki burger is my all time favorite. Prices are justified and right now theyre giving 10% off to the students. Their chai gives me vibe of India not gonna lie. It has became my every day stop for chai before college. I would definitely recommend this place trust me you wont regret !

But once I tried it at this restaurant, I fell in love with it     The staff was really nice too and the order turnaround time was pretty quick. The vibe at this place reminded me of home. I would definitely come back here to try more food options!
I am glad Vancouver Downtown got new place with Delhi Vibe. There Authentic Chai and Chicken Momos remind me of Delhi. Best Indian street food that too available in cheap price. Keep it up guys

One of the finest Indian restaurants i have been to. Food is Awesome!! Perfect for a family dinner!! Perfect vibe !! Last but not least, the staff is so kind and helpful !! Just to know parking is less due to downtown.

i went there today for the first time I tried different items and all were great but the aloo tikki burger was greatest I would say. Enjoyed it loved it .
Nice guy working. Good chai. Nice to be able to get snacks that arent typically available - enjoyed the papri chaat. Quick and reasonably priced.
It was my first visit but its gonna be my daily visit for sure best indian taste all over Vancouver especially the employess over there one of them were Varsha Fab guys Food

oh i really like this palace and food... specially the service of kritika ... she helps us to select the yummy food items

Me and my friend tried couple of items, all of them were very good especially aloo tikki burger, paneer wrap and butter chicken bowl. The guy serving at the front was very courteous and helpful! We will be back for sure.

Food was delicious! Very well made and has the right amount of spice. We had the fried chicken Momos, veg Momos, bun egg, and karak chai. I will say, if you cant handle spice, be aware that the Momos are definitely spicy. But in the proper flavourful way, not the north American burn your mouth heat way. Bun Egg was delicious. Egg had a nice caramelized exterior and a creamy eggy interior. The dhaniya chutney inside really added the extra umph as one would associate with an anda pav. Karak Chai tasted exactly how I make my cha at home! Full body, creamy, but not over steeped and bitter. Be aware that karak chai is strong brewed tea boiled with milk, NOT masala chai that most north Americans associate chai with. They do have masala chai on the menu, so go for that if thats more of your thing.
Good food great staff! I was attended by Kritika and the experience was superb!!
Great food. Loves the momos, spring rolls, buel puri and chai. Authentic taste with an amazing service.
Seating can be improved more. And music would sound better if speakers are placed in the whole area. Otherwise everything great.
